Philippine Stocks Movers: DMCI, Greenergy, Lepanto, Pancake

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-09-01T04:25:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/dmci-greenergy-jollibee-pancake-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index increased 0.4 percent
to 4,366.59.  Gold producers:  Lepanto Consolidated Mining (LCB)  Co.’s Class A
shares (LC PM), which are reserved for Filipinos, sank 8.1
percent to 1.48 pesos, the lowest close since Aug. 17 as the
price of the precious metal slid for the second day. Lepanto
Class B shares (LCB PM), which have no ownership restrictions,
decreased 5.9 percent to 1.61 pesos, the lowest since Aug. 19.
 Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s biggest metals
producer, declined 1.1 percent to 27.40 pesos.  Gold for immediate delivery decreased 0.2 percent to
$1,823.07 an ounce earlier today. The metal lost 0.5 percent
yesterday.  DMCI Holdings Inc. (DMC)  , the nation’s biggest
construction company, climbed 3.1 percent to 41.50 pesos, the
sharpest gain since Aug. 16. The property unit of the company
may book 18 billion pesos ($425 million) in sales this year,
driven by consumers’ “positive response” to its projects, DMCI
said in a stock exchange filing.  Greenergy Holdings Inc. (GREEN PM) jumped 18 percent to 1.3
centavos, the sharpest gain since October 2008. The Manila-based
company will form a joint venture with  China ’s Tianjin Tianbao
Investment and Development Corp. that will invest at least $1.3
billion in Philippine wind energy projects over a 10-year
period, a stock exchange filing showed. The venture will invest
up to $200 million within the first two years, Greenergy said.  Pancake House Inc. (PCKH PM) climbed 17 percent to 10.50
pesos, the highest close since Oct. 19. The Manila-based company
signed an agreement to acquire pizza brand Yellow Cab for 800
million pesos, Chairman Martin Lorenzo said. Pancake House
traded for the first time since Aug. 15.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
